race.comment: PATH TO PROFIT (12) should take some beating. She was just edged out on debut as favourite at Bairnsdale before a good effort in a stronger maiden at Sandown Hillside when beaten under a length. She draws ideally and gets every chance to break through. UYUNI (14) has placed in both runs to date, getting back as favourite over this route last time out, beaten two lengths. Like her getting to 1200m now, she should be ready to break through with even luck. RAVENS BAY (6) presents third up having showed nice improvement at Ballarat last time out when showing the way and sticking on gamely. She should bounce to the front and take catching. TRUE SERENITY (13) and BLONDIE'S AWARD (7) were both well beaten on debut in their respective 1000m races, both should be far better suited up in trip.
